rest_of_day_open: The rest of my week should go really well. I only have 2 days of work, so I get to enjoy some time off. I also am going on a date with the wife on Saturday. critical_positive: She seemed extremely friendly and had some fun things to talk about involving her cultural background. She was younger and didn't really seem to be as socially awkward as some of the people that I have spoken to in that past. Even though I did much of the heavy lifting in the conversation, I think that she probably would have been fine to help carry on the conversation.
critical_negative: I probably am guilty of doing most of the heavy lifting in asking questions and follow up questions during this conversation. If I wouldn't have been so aggressive in asking so many questions, it might have been easier for her to ask me questions. I also found that I would prompt information about myself really without her asking for it which might be annoying.

rest_of_day_open: The rest of my week will be fairly busy because I have work as well as having to study for my classes because exams and finals are coming up in the next few weeks. Other than that, I think I will be able to get enough sleep this week which will make me feel happier.
critical_positive: What worked well about this conversation was that we both seemed genuinely interested in what the other had to say and were polite and friendly. We seemed "genuinely interested" because it was clear we were both listening to each other when the other talked, and we were both friendly on the same level.
critical_negative: Something that didn't work well was that at times it seemed like I was cutting him off in conversation too quickly, because there were a few times where I would start speaking while he was speaking. I think that made the conversation feel really choppy, whereas he was actually going into depth about the topics.
